    {
      "id": "f781e15e_7d774a1e",
      "file_path": "components/model-catalog/blueprint-model/test-blueprint/capability_restconf/Definitions/activation-blueprint.json",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 177,
      "message": "My reasoning was that first I would need to send a mount command. After that, I would need to send the configlet and then conclude everything with an unmount.\n\nThe first prefix is for me to load the mount request and mesh it with the values I need. That would be the first payload I would send.\n\nThe configlet itself would have been persisted already meshed, so it would be just a matter of sending it.\n\nThe last step would be to create the unmount request, and for that I would need the mapping and the template related to the unmount.\n\nHypothetical example in Python:\n\n rc = RestconfClient(...)\n rr = ResolutionHelper(self)\n\n # mounting device\n mount_payload = rr.resolve_and_generate_message_from_template_prefix(\"configure-restconf-mount\")\n rc.mount(mount_payload)\n\n # recover and send configlet\n configlet = #recover configlet somehow\n rc.configure(configlet)\n\n # unounting device\n unmount_payload = rr.resolve_and_generate_message_from_template_prefix(\"configure-restconf-unmount\")\n rc.unmount(unmount_payload)\n\n\nThat is the reason why I have created this.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5060,
        "name": "Rodrigo Ottero",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ottero@gmail.com",
        "username": "ottero"
      },
      "updated": "2019-03-05 17:38:54.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "62a49cf9_b607ffe0",
      "unresolved": false
    },
